 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Lannseax's Glaive</strong>&nbsp;is an <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Incantations" href="/Incantations" target="">Incantation</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Lannseax's Glaive</strong> is used to make a sweeping attack with a red lightning glaive. Updated to&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Incantation that channels the power of the ancient dragon Lansseax.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Creates a red-lightning glaive and sweeps the area from above.<br>This attack unleashes trails of lightning.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Lansseax was the sister of Fortissax. It is said that she took the form of a human to commune with the knights as a priestess of the ancient dragon cult.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Lansseax's Glaive</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Lansseax's Glaive</strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ancient Dragon Lansseax" href="/Ancient+Dragon+Lansseax">Ancient Dragon Lansseax</a>. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=6387&amp;lat=-96.32031&amp;lng=96.44973&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=6387&amp;lat=-96.32031&amp;lng=96.44973&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Interactive Map Link</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Lansseax's Glaive&nbsp;Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Stamina Cost: 55</li> 
 <li>Deals lightning damage</li> 
 <li>One of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dragon Cult Incantations" href="/Dragon+Cult+Incantations">Dragon Cult Incantations</a> and is boosted by the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Gravel Stone Seal" href="/Gravel+Stone+Seal">Gravel Stone Seal</a></li> 
 <li>Long cast time followed by a large horizontal "glaive" swipe, with follow-up AoE damage.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Should be treated as an AoE spell for dealing with groups, as&nbsp;the damage is mediocre for single targets.</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff6600;"><em>Note:</em></span> FP cost reduced by 21% as of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>, from 28 to 22</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
